e been the son of Ralph [I] de Somery, who witnessed the foundation charter of Dudley priory (see above).  m as her first husband, HAWISE Paynell, daughter of RALPH Paynell of Dudley & his wife --- (-after 1210).  “Hawys Paganella” confirmed donations to Tykford Priory by \"Johannes de Sumeri vir meus\" by undated charter, witnessed by “Radulfo de Sumeri filio meo”[678].   She married secondly ([1196/97]) Roger de Berkeley.  “Hawis Paynel” donated property to Tykford Priory, with the consent of “domini mei Rogeri de Berkele”, for the soul of “Gervasii Paynel fratris mei”, by undated charter[679].   \n\nThey may or not be his parents according to Charles Cawley.\nhttp://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ENGLISHNOBILITYMEDIEVAL3P-S.htm#RalphSomerydied1210","sourceList":[{"title":"John de Somery - MyHeritage ","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.myheritage.com/research/record-40001-260852912/john-de-somery-in-familysearch-family-tree?s=347994791&fspid=MFVK-8PY","sourceUri":"QF4D-7RR"},{"title":"John de Somery - Medlands - FMG","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/ENGLISHNOBILITYMEDIEVAL3P-S.htm#RalphSomerydied1210","sourceUri":"QXK7-278"},{"title":"Coat of Arms - Somery","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://wappenwiki.org/index.php?title=File:FW111_Somery.svg","sourceUri":"QXK7-V1V"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1125","date":"1125","place":"Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1151","date":"1151","place":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England","age":"26","id":"2M5Y-3XL"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1162","date":"about 1162","place":"Staffordshire, England","age":"37","id":"GWM5-HNF"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1161","date":"after 1161","age":"37","id":"9CC8-TJ6"},{"name":"Death","sources":"2","year":"1191","date":"about 1191","place":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England,","age":"66"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"