ley, Worcestershire, England","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England","Dudley, Worcestershire, England,":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1125–about 1191":"1125–circa 1191","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1151–1211":"1151–1211","1162–Female":"1162–Overleden","1100–1161":"1100–1161","1104–Female":"1104–Overleden","about 1162":"circa 1162","about 1191":"circa 1191","after 1161":"na 1161","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1161":"1161","1191":"1191","bef 1125":"vóór 1125","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1211":"1211","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1209":"1209","Dudley, Worcestershire, England":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England","Dudley, Worcestershire, England,":"Dudley, Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1125–about 1191":"1125–about 1191","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1151–1211":"1151–1211","1162–Female":"1162–Deceased","1100–1161":"1100–1161","1104–Female":"1104–Deceased","about 1162":"about 1162","about 1191":"about 1191","after 1161":"after 1161","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1161":"1161","1191":"1191","bef 1125":"before 1125","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1211":"1211","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1209":"1209","Dudley, Worcestershire, England":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England","Dudley, Worcestershire, England,":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Somery","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Abelino, Adela, Alberto, Alfredo, Ana, Angel, Asuncion, Domingo, Elena, Emiliano, Emilio, Eusebio.","Spanish: possibly a habitational name from La Somera in Cuenca province, named from <i>somero</i> ‘shallow’. This surname is most common in the Philippines."],"variants":[]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John de Somery was born in 1125, in Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England, his father, Ralph de Somery, was 26 and his mother, Lady de Somery, was 22. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Hawise Paynel. He died about 1191, in Dudley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1125–about 1191":"1125–umbes 1191","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1151–1211":"1151–1211","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1100–1161":"1100–1161","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","about 1162":"umbes 1162","about 1191":"umbes 1191","after 1161":"pärast 1161","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1161":"1161","1191":"1191","bef 1125":"enne 1125","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1211":"1211","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1209":"1209","Dudley, Worcestershire, England":"Dudley, Worcestershire, England","England":"England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England","Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Little Crawley, Buckinghamshire, England","Dudley, Worcestershire, England,":"Dudley, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1125–about 1191":"1125–noin 1191","1125–1191":"1125–1191","1144–1209":"1144–1209","1151–1211":"1151–1211","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","1100–1161":"1100–1161","1104–Female":"1104–Kuollut","about 1162":"noin 1162","about 1191":"noin 1191","after 1161":"1161 jälkeen","1151":"1151","1162":"1162","1161":"1161","1191":"1191","bef 1125":"ennen vuotta 1125","1104":"1104","1125":"1125","1211":"1211","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1209":"1209","Dudley, Worcestershire, Englan